        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 4:21PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Trinity Junction, or 24 miles north of Fallon,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Battleground Point and Desert Peak.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
